                    <h1 style="margin-bottom:20px;">Welcome to Pizza site</h1>
                    	<p style="line-height:1.7em; margin-bottom:1.5em;">Pizza is a flat, round, disc shaped bread that is topped with a number of toppings that include usually mozzarella cheese, tomato sauce, and a variety of other toppings depending on the culture and the recipe.</p>
                        <p style="line-height:1.7em; margin-bottom:1.5em;">It is originally a part of the Neapolitan cuisine and the dish later became popular in many parts of the world. Since the original recipe of the pizza, there have been many a variations in the recipes. A place or an establishment that makes and sells pizzas is known as pizzeria.</p>
                        <p style="line-height:1.7em; margin-bottom:1.5em;">The other phrases such as pizza parlor and pizza house and pizza place are the ones used in the United States. Pizza Pie is a term used for the purpose of simplicity, as may be in the staff of the pizzeria.</p>

